&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discord has a highly engaged community of millions of daily active users who use the platform for many different reasons, but there’s one thing that nearly everyone does: &lt;strong&gt;play video games.&lt;/strong&gt; Discord plays a uniquely important role in the future of gaming, and we are focused on making it easier and more fun for people to hang out before, during, and after playing games.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;At the heart of Discord&#39;s communities is Safety. The Safety team at Discord is responsible for ensuring users find belonging by minimizing exposure to abuse on the platform. We&#39;re looking for a Product Manager to lead our work on scaled abuse — fake accounts, account takeovers, scraping — and help keep Discord a safe and welcoming place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to our safety Group Product Manager, you&#39;ll create the vision, build the systems, and lead the cross-functional strategy that detects and prevents scaled abuse before it reaches our users. This is a high-ownership, high-impact role with significant room to shape strategy, drive investment, and define how we measure and win in this space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the product philosophy, vision, and multi-quarter roadmap for scaled abuse, spanning fake accounts, ATO, scraping, and recidivism detection — prioritizing proactive, foundational investments that compound across the platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, own, and socialize the north-star metrics for the space and report progress against those goals to the relevant stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate threat research into forward-looking defensive product work, so our roadmap focus’s on the highest-leverage defensive investments rather than one-off firefights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-functional execution with growth, security, anti-abuse and product teams to minimize impact of abuse on our users. This work spans machine learning solutions, heuristics, and building delightful features in-app.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product teams across Discord to embed abuse resistance into new surfaces before they ship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you should have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
